<br>
Peleus, being mortal, was unsure exactly of Eris's powers and watched her carefully.  He jumped as she slapped him and then continued to watch her as she began to move among the Goddesses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/23/01 4:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/qherarpg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Arrival of Eris</span><hr size=1> As her daughter appeared, Hera watched her carefully.  She had known there was no way to keep a Goddess or God from knowing when the Olympians congregated.  It was like a great power being given off to all immortal.  Her pale icy blue eyes danced over to her other two daughters who quietly watched the middle child.<br>
<br>
Hebe held Eiliethyia in her arms gently.  The two had become close, the eldest and youngest children of the King of the Gods.  Hebe, always the quiet and calmest of the children of couple, frowned watching her sister quietly.  As Eilie smiled gently, excited that something interesting might actually be happening.  It had gotten a little boring as everyone had begun to eat.<br>
<br>
Hera took in a deep breath as her daughter seemed to be on the prowl.  She folded her arms in front of her and wandered exactly what kind of game Eris was wanting to play between she, Aphrodite and Athena.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, tell us daughter.  What exactly is on your mind?&quot; <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/unikeqofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NikeQofV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/23/01 7:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.btinternet.com/~dave.newton/lysette-anthony/pictures/lysette-anthony109.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arrival of Eris</span><hr size=1> ::Shakes her head and laughs and says to Athena, Artemis and Aphrodite:: Forget her girls, this isn't about Eris, its a about the wedding and preventing anything or &quot;anyone&quot; from spoiling this occaision ::smiles at them all reassuringly. Walks over to the couple::<br>
